radition, his name appears as <i>Patricius</i> ‘patrician’ (i.e. belonging to the Roman senatorial or noble class), but this may actually represent a Latinized form of some lost Celtic (British) name. In Ireland in particular, it has been one of the most enduringly popular boys' names."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"spouse Patrick DeHome married Patrick DeHome before 1190, in Europe. They were the parents of at least 1 son."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","1170–1248":"1170–1248","1190–1266":"1190–1266","–Female":"Surnud","1190":"1190","1248":"1248","1266":"1266","before 1190":"enne 1190","1170":"1170","Europe":"Europe","Home, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Home, Berwickshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","1170–1248":"1170–1248","1190–1266":"1190–1266","–Female":"Kuollut","1190":"1190","1248":"1248","1266":"1266","before 1190":"ennen vuotta 1190","1170":"1170","Europe":"Europe","Home, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Home, Berwickshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"–":"Décédée","1170–1248":"1170–1248","1190–1266":"1190–1266","–Female":"Décédée","1190":"1190","1248":"1248","1266":"1266","before 1190":"avant 1190","1170":"1170","Europe":"Europe","Home, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Home, Berwickshire, Écosse","lifeSummary":"spouse Patrick DeHome a épousé Patrick DeHome avant 1190, à Europe. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","1170–1248":"1170–1248","1190–1266":"1190–1266","–Female":"Verstorben","1190":"1190","1248":"1248","1266":"1266","before 1190":"vor 1190","1170":"1170","Europe":"Europa","Home, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Home, Berwickshire, Scotland","lifeSummary":"spouse Patrick DeHome hat vor 1190 in Europa Patrick DeHome geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","1170–1248":"1170–1248","1190–1266":"1190–1266","–Female":"Desede","1190":"1190","1248":"1248","1266":"1266","before 1190":"before 1190","1170":"1170","Europe":"Europe","Home, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Home, Berwickshire, Scotland"},"hu":{"–":"elhunyt","1170–1248":"1170–1248","1190–1266":"1190–1266","–Fem